# Chat Support (Claude + Supabase + Kognitos API Tools)

## Architecture

```
App sidebar "Conversations" group (client) ↔ useChat hook ↔ ChatProvider context
  → POST /api/chat → Claude (Anthropic) with API tools → Kognitos REST API
  → SSE stream back to client
  → Messages persisted in Supabase
```

Sessions and messages persist in Supabase. Claude answers questions using **registered API tools only** — it never runs arbitrary code. The chat UI lives at `/chat` with conversation history in the app sidebar.

## Registered Tools

| Tool | API endpoint | Purpose |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `list_automations` | GET /automations | List all automations in the workspace |
| `get_automation` | GET /automations/{id} | Get automation code, connections, inputs |
| `list_runs` | GET /automations/{id}/runs | List batch history with statuses |
| `get_run` | GET /automations/{id}/runs/{runId} | Full run details: decoded outputs, errors |

To add a new tool, define an `Anthropic.Tool` in the `TOOLS` array in `app/api/chat/route.ts` and add its handler to the `executeTool` switch. Update the system prompt in `lib/chat/system-prompt.ts` to describe it.

## Required env vars

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — Claude API key
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` — Supabase project URL
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — Supabase anon key
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — Supabase service role key (server-side only)
- `KOGNITOS_TOKEN` — Kognitos API bearer token

## Required npm packages

- `@anthropic-ai/sdk` — Anthropic Claude SDK
- `@supabase/supabase-js` — Supabase client
- `react-markdown` — Markdown rendering in chat bubbles
- `remark-gfm` — GFM support (tables, strikethrough, task lists)
- `@tailwindcss/typography` — Prose styling for rendered markdown

## Supabase Schema (CRITICAL — project-specific table names)

Tables are defined in `supabase/migrations/00000000000001_chat.sql`.

**Table names MUST be prefixed with the project name** (e.g. `provider_claims_chat_sessions`) to avoid collisions when multiple apps share the same Supabase instance. Use `snake_case` of the project's short name as the prefix.

Example for a project called "Provider Claims":

- **provider_claims_chat_sessions** — id, user_id, title, created_at, updated_at
- **provider_claims_chat_messages** — id, session_id, role (user/assistant/tool), content, tool_call (jsonb), created_at

RLS is enabled with permissive policies. Cascade delete from sessions to messages.

## Session Auto-Titling (CRITICAL)

Sessions must NOT stay as "New conversation". After the first user–assistant exchange, use Claude to generate a concise title (max 6 words) from the user's message.

In `app/api/chat/route.ts`, after persisting the assistant response, check if it's the first exchange (message count ≤ 2). If so, call Claude with a short prompt like:

```
Generate a short title (max 6 words) for a chat that starts with this message. Return ONLY the title, no quotes or punctuation.

User message: {message}
```

Update the session title in Supabase with the result. This runs after the main response stream, so it doesn't slow down the chat.

